Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSelectedPtnPinGuide(25.10)                    setSelectedPtnPinGuide(25.10)

Name
       setSelectedPtnPinGuide - Sets area, name, and layer Id for the selected
       pin guide object

Syntax
       setSelectedPtnPinGuide

       [-help]

       <x1><y1><x2><y2>

       <ptnPinObj>

       <layerID><space>

       [<cellName>]

       Sets area, name, and layer Id for the selected pin guide object.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSelectedPtnPinGuide parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSelectedPtnPinGuide

       <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the pin guide area.

       <ptnPinObj>
              Specifies  the  name of the net, net group, or pin group associ-
              ated with this pin guide

       <layerID>
              Specifies the metal layer(s) for the pin guide.

       <space>
              Specifies spacing for the pin guide.

       <cellName>
              This parameter is required only if the object specified with the
              <ptnPinObj> parameter is a pin group. Specifies the name of  the
              cell with which the pin group is associated.

Example
              * The following command sets the partition pin guide, ptnGuide2,
                within  the  specified area and on the layers 2 (Metal2) and 3
                (Metal3) with pin guide spacing as 0 and associated  with  the
                cell cell1:

                selectPtnPinGuide  100.0  100.0  150.0 150.0 pinGuide2 {2 3} 0
                {cell1}

